  "summary": "Benign canary package with no installer-side impact",
  "details": "Package's postinstall hook and main entry both invoke runPrepare() in lib/warmup.js, which sets an in-memory flag and prints '[trap:prepare] hook executed' to stdout. There is no network I/O, no filesystem access beyond module require, no shell execution, and no reading of environment variables or credentials. The '[trap:]' marker and the package's repository field pointing at an unrelated upstream (tim-kos/node-retry) suggest this is a research/canary package rather than a functional retry library, but the observable behavior is harmless.",
